            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">5. You see a 48-year-old lorry driver, who presents to you with a three-month history of heartburn after meals which has not been settling with antacids and PPIs. You suspect that the patient has a hiatus hernia. The most appropriate investigation for diagnosing a hiatus hernia is:</p>"
