            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">6. You see a 56-year-old man who was admitted for an elective upper GI endoscopyn due to longstanding GORD which has failed to improve on antacids and PPIs. Your registrar suspects that this patient may have Barrett’s oesophagus and asks you to define what this is. The most appropriate description of Barrett’s oesophagus is:</p>"
